snippet.title: Microsoft's Cortana doesn’t speak Spanish, for now
snippet.description: The virtual personal assistant to be released with the new Windows Phone 8.1 update will speak in English and then Chinese. Spanish won’t be available until 2015.

snippet.title: Apple loses iPad suit to Spanish tablet maker
snippet.description: Interestingly, the complaint Apple lodged apparently concerned the same design right that it asserted in its fight against Samsung.

snippet.title: Amazon Kindle bookstore now available in Spanish
snippet.description: Dubbed "eBooks Kindle en Espanol," the new e-book store will offer Spanish-language books and publications.

snippet.title: Nokia's Lumia means, um, 'prostitute' in Spanish
snippet.description: It's not the most colloquial Spanish term, but dictionaries suggest that Nokia's new phone name has money-for-pleasure connotations.

snippet.title: Anonymous takes down Spanish police site
snippet.description: According to El Mundo, the country's national police site was down for an hour on Saturday--a day after the announcement of the arrest of three alleged hackers in Spain.

snippet.title: Spanish ERP company flexes open-source muscle
snippet.description: Openbravo CEO talks about the transition from Oracle to open source and from CTO to CEO.

snippet.title: Tech jobs hold up as unemployment rate rises
snippet.description: It's hard to find bright spots in newly released labor statistics, but here's one: there are more computer systems design and consulting services gigs than a year ago.

snippet.title: Twitter translates into Spanish
snippet.description: A Spanish-language version of the site is the first non-English translation of the site to be rolled out as part of a new internationalization effort.

snippet.title: Apple loses iPad lawsuit to tiny Spanish tablet maker
snippet.description: Apple has lost a legal battle against NT-K, a small Spanish manufacturer that made an Android tablet.

snippet.title: Fume hoods leave the stove and join the unemployment line
snippet.description: Downdraft cook tops from Jenn-Air eliminate the need for fume hoods
